<font size=4><font color=</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utuvedstormrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tuved Stormrunner</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0> at: 2/4/02 2:31:35 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utatankawd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatankawd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 164<br> <font color=#333399>(2/25/02 2:24:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2692.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Does the lvl54 Form of the Howler add mana regen??</span><hr size=1> Recently got a 2nd PC and rolled up a pocket chanter.  Just for the heck of it I did some mana regen/medding tests, and came up with 2 things that surprised me, and a comment to add to this discussion:<br>
<br>
1 - Ran a test with OOM to FM, with no mana buffs of any kind.  Actually, I noted the mana bar at minute intervals, after the last one before FM, estimated the %-age mana filled, divided by minutes, converted to mana/tick.  Used the accepted formula for mana pool.  Came up with exactly 21 mana/tick from medding with no mana regen.  I was VERY surprised, I thought the base medding rate with 252 med skill was better than 21/tick.  I was thinking it was more in the 25/tick range.  This makes things like clarity and FT items even more desirable.<br>
<br>
2 - Ran same exact test with FotH up, results were exactly 23 mana/tick.  This indicates that FotH really does add 2/tick mana regen.<br>
<br>
3 - Ran the test again with FotH and Clarity from my level 34 enchanter.  According to Casters Realm, a level 34 clarity adds 7/tick mana regen.  Well, my results showed 28 mana/tick, indicating a 5/tick benefit from Clarity.  So the question is, does clarity ever give more than 5 mana/tick, and if so, what level does the chanter need to be?<br>
<br>
Once I decide to PL my chanter some more, I will test again.<br>
<br>
Tat<br>
<br>
Edit - Just noticed, it says by level 35 that clarity adds 7/tick.  Guess I need to spend another hour PLing my chanter =) <p>Tatanka WolfDancer, 57th Druid<BR>
