<br>
The way it used to be (and probably still is), the effect of clarity went up with the caster's level.  You will not see this on caster's realm or by reading files on your computer, because it's one of the many server-side spell effects that people seem to ignore.  I have a vague recollection that it's something like 4/tick at 29 and up to 7/tick at 50, but I can't tell you for sure.  I remember this was also a problem with the level 52 group clarity, because it started off giving less mana than regular clarity, and by the time it reached regular clarity (about level 56), the caster already had clarity II available.  I remember raising this issue on the caster's realm enchanter forum some years ago, try searching there. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A> at: 2/25/02 10:18:43 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utatankawd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatankawd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 165<br> <font color=#333399>(2/25/02 1:28:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2692.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Does the lvl54 Form of the Howler add mana regen??</span><hr size=1> I understand it goes up with the casters level.  Clarity is a level 29 spell, and doesn't supposedly reach full potential until level 35 (I mistakenly thought 34, so I stopped PLing my chanter at 34).  My question was, at what level does clarity reach its full potential?  Since I noticed the level &quot;35&quot; comment on casters realm AFTER I wrote the post, I know that I have at least one more level to go.  I will post an update once the chanter is 35.<br>
<br>
Tat<br>
